OL,3,CAdams jury not asked to give 'verdict
OL,4,Con Irish history'
OL,6,FJurors in the Gerry Adams libel action
OL,7,Fagainst the BBC are not being asking
OL,8,Fto pass verdict on Irish history, a
OL,9,Fjudge has said.
OL,11,FDelivering his instructions to the
OL,12,Fjury members on Friday, Judge Mr
OL,13,FJustice Alexander Owens told them they
OL,14,Fwere not being asked to make a
OL,15,Fdecision as journalists, but as
OL,16,F"ordinary members of the public".
OL,18,FIn his charge to the jurors, the judge
OL,19,Fmade clear they were not tasked with
OL,20,Fmaking a "historical judgment" on Mr
OL,21,FAdams' role in the peace process.
