OL,6,FThe BBC has stood by the programme and
OL,7,Fhas argued it was entitled to put
OL,8,Fforward matters raised in the
OL,9,Fdocumentary, which it says were of
OL,10,Fpublic importance and done in good
OL,11,Ffaith.
OL,13,FThe corporation has argued the meaning
OL,14,Fof the programme and article was not
OL,15,Fthat Mr Adams had sanctioned and
OL,16,Fapproved the killing, and that the
OL,17,Fclaim had to be taken in context of
OL,18,Fthe whole report.
